sentences: Alexandra Prince (born 1975) is a German singer and songwriter.
Her first solo single "How we livin" was a top 30 hit and stayed in the German Charts for a full 16 weeks.
Alexandra Prince became a massive international club hit in 2005, Alexandra earned a place as an established, well-respected house diva.
Currently, Alexandra is working together with major house music producers from around the world in the making of her debut album.

It is debated that she may also have been the true singing voice behind Fernanda Brandão from Hot Banditoz and the '90s German teen pop star Blümchen, with Prince providing the higher vocals, while Jasmin Wagner took the spoken/shouted parts.
